OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FIran jails Belgian aid     
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fworker for 28 years -      
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Ffamily                     
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Iran has sentenced a Belgian aid worker
OL,6, to 28 years in prison on unknown       
OL,7, charges, his family has said.          
OL,9,FOlivier Vandecasteele, 41, was arrested
OL,10,Fduring a brief visit to Tehran in      
OL,11,FFebruary and accused of espionage.     
OL,13,FOn Wednesday, his family said they had 
OL,14,Fbeen informed of his sentence at a     
OL,15,Fmeeting with Belgium's prime minister. 
OL,17,FThere was no confirmation from Iran,   
OL,18,Fbut the news comes days after Belgium's
OL,19,Fconstitutional court halted a          
OL,20,Fcontroversial prisoner exchange treaty.
